  "notes": "Captured live 2026-04 evidence for `metaobjectBulkDelete(where: { ids })` deleting one selected row from a disposable definition while leaving two unselected rows visible. The proxy replay earns setup state through public definition and entry create mutations, then compares the id-scoped bulk-delete payload plus immediate ID, connection, and definition readback. Type-scoped bulk-delete parity separately asserts definition-count readback."
